Filmmaker Sekinat Usman Ovayioza’s new project, ‘Idamu Adugbo’ is currently making waves on Youtube. The didactic and intriguing flick starring Peju Ogunmola, Rotimi Salami, Sunday Jatto, Aina Gold, Olayinka Solomon, Saidat Munirat Usman, and Sola Olaibi among others is the fourth of outstanding movies that Sekinat has produced. The other three are; Shekinah, Dangerous Wedding, and Eru.   Teddy A: BBNaija not for you if…     Why I’m not involved in politics, by Burna Boy     Afrobeats breaking barriers, Nigeria in worst condition ever…   Speaking about her unusual role, Sekinat who also starred in the movie said, “It’s a challenging role that people never expected from me to perform because I and the character are opposite of ourselves and this made people start posting it in which is currently going viral. The storyline of this movie is uncommon and fascinating because I got it as an inspiration to teach the world against bad act and drugs and to be kind and supportive to people so that you won’t become an enemy to those that need your help. The story is full of in-depth analysis which I’m sure the world would love it.” ‘Idamu Adugbo’ is directed by Wasiu Adeyanju (de Genius) and marketed by Small world international.